THE WINES OF GERMANY

All wine experts agree that the best German wines are superb, and are possibly among the best white wines of the world. Even the less expensive ones are charming and have finesse.

The latitude of the German vineyards extend as far north as Labrador. Grapes struggle to survive, but when they do, they are superb. The most important areas are the vineyards that overlook the Rhine and Moselle Rivers. We take these wines sufficiently seriously to offer you, after many visits and tastings, those that we consider the best of Germany.
